  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Despite its publication by Leuven University Press in 2020, \"Dialogen over Belgi\u00eb\" has not yet generated academic citations or community discourse across major social platforms. However, it demonstrates robust commercial linkage through its presence on platforms like Amazon and Goodreads, suggesting a degree of public interest.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Dialogen over Belgi\u00eb,\" published in 2020, presents a critical exploration of themes relevant to Belgian society. While the text has not accrued any citations to date, it is noteworthy for its significant commercial linkage. The book is available on retail platforms such as Amazon and Goodreads, indicating a potential engagement with a wider audience beyond academic circles.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The absence of discussion on platforms like Wikipedia, Reddit, and Bluesky reflects a lack of online community engagement at this time. This is a crucial observation, as such discussions often contribute to the broader visibility and impact of scholarly works. Despite this, the fact that there are no reported events or mentions suggests that the book remains largely within academic confines.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Even though the usage landscape and attention signals are currently uncharted, the book's presence in commercial spaces hints at its relevance in public discourse. The alignment with themes concerning sustainability and policy is discernible, demonstrated by its association with at least one Sustainable Development Goal, underlining the potential for future application in policy discussions.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Going forward, it may be beneficial for the authors and the publisher to actively promote \"Dialogen over Belgi\u00eb\" in various forums to stimulate discussion and engagement. Enhancing visibility through social media or academic conferences could foster needed discourse, facilitating a pathway for scholarly uptake and community interaction.</p>",
